      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 33.67430782783208,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "text": "1.  Read the problem  ->  map each objective to the\nright tool / data structure (the list above).\n2.  Design the desk UI first: glassmorphism panels,\nLED backlight, grain-noise texture, the brand banner.\n3.  Build client-side parsers: Mammoth.js for DOCX,\nPDF.js for PDF, plain readers for md / txt / json.\n4.  Make the work VISIBLE: render references as an\ninteractive directed graph + a plain-English trail:\n        WT-01  ->  WT-02  ->  WT-03.\n5.  Add SHA-256 auditing + a session log so every\nscan stays verifiable and tamper-evident.\n6.  Add Word export + a pre-composed Gmail draft so\ndata leaves the app only when the user chooses.\n7.  Wire Navbar + sidebars, polish responsive CSS,\nthen push everything to GitHub.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1.  Read the problem  ->  map each objective to the\nright tool / data structure (the list above).\n2.  Design the desk UI first: glassmorphism panels,\nLED backlight, grain-noise texture, the brand banner.\n3.  Build client-side parsers: Mammoth.js for DOCX,\nPDF.js for PDF, plain readers for md / txt / json.\n4.  Make the work VISIBLE: render references as an\ninteractive directed graph + a plain-English trail:\n        WT-01  ->  WT-02  ->  WT-03.\n5.  Add SHA-256 auditing + a session log so every\nscan stays verifiable and tamper-evident.\n6.  Add Word export + a pre-composed Gmail draft so\ndata leaves the app only when the user chooses.\n7.  Wire Navbar + sidebars, polish responsive CSS,\nthen push everything to GitHub.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 13,
      "index": "aH",
      "autoResize": false
    },
